commentary: Murtagh to Mohammad Shahzad, OUT leading edge caught at mid-off Shahzad is staying put, he thinks it might have bounced in front of the fielder. And the umpires think so too, with the soft signal being not out. This was angled into Shahzad and he wanted to flick it away, but a hint of movement meant he got the leading edge. Cameron-Dow at mid-off ran in and went low to grab the ball. But does he have fingers underneath the ball? He certainly appears to have done so. And the third umpire agrees! Shahzad has to go. Six off the first ball, out off the fourth.

commentary: Simi Singh to Asghar Afghan, 3 runs scooped very fine. Cheeky shot, he went down and picked it up from outside off and sent it over his left shoulder. Good work by Paul Stirling on the fine leg fence. He ran across, and dived, got a hand to the ball and pushed it back. The momentum took him over the ropes and he athletically dived back in to parry the ball away from the boundary once again. Brilliant work, he's saved a run for his team, and shown excellent athleticism and commitment
shortText: Simi Singh to Asghar Afghan, 3 runs
text: scooped very fine. Cheeky shot, he went down and picked it up from outside off and sent it over his left shoulder. Good work by Paul Stirling on the fine leg fence. He ran across, and dived, got a hand to the ball and pushed it back. The momentum took him over the ropes and he athletically dived back in to parry the ball away from the boundary once again. Brilliant work, he's saved a run for his team, and shown excellent athleticism and commitment

Important wicket for Ireland.
